text: Tinker Hill is a summit in Putnam County, in the U.S. state of New York. It has an elevation of . The hill was named for the fact that a jack of all trades, or a "tinkering" man, settled there ca. 1800. ==References== Category:Hills of New York (state) Category:Mountains of Putnam County, New York Category:Mountains of New York (state) Category:Geography of Putnam County, New York
title: Tinker Hill
